label.value: NMB Gene

value.value: This gene is involved in smooth muscle contraction.

label.value: NMB wt Allele

value.value: Human NMB wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 15q25.2 and is approximately 3 kb in length. This allele, which encodes neuromedin-B precursor protein, plays a role in the regulation of smooth muscle contraction.

label.value: NMB Gene Product

value.value: A protein encoded by the NMB gene.

label.value: Neuromedin-B Precursor

value.value: Neuromedin-B precursor (121 aa, ~13 kDa) is encoded by the human NMB gene. This protein is involved in smooth muscle contraction.

label.value: Neuromedin-B

value.value: Neuromedin-B (10 aa, ~1 kDa) is encoded by the human NMB gene. This protein plays a role in the stimulation of smooth muscle contraction.

label.value: ESRRB Gene

value.value: This gene plays a role in transcriptional regulation of genes that regulate the maintainance of self-renewal and pluripotency of embryonic and trophoblast stem cells.

label.value: ESRRB wt Allele

value.value: Human ESRRB wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 14q24.3 and is approximately 191 kb in length. This allele, which encodes steroid hormone receptor ERR2 protein, is involved in rod cell survival and inner ear development. Mutation of the gene is associated with autosomal recessive deafness type 35.

label.value: Steroid Hormone Receptor ERR2

value.value: Steroid hormone receptor ERR2 (508 aa, ~56 kDa) is encoded by the human ESRRB gene. This protein plays a role in inner ear development, stem cell maintenance and rod cell survival.
A chromosome band present on 2q

label.value: SLC39A4 Gene

value.value: This gene is involved in zinc homeostasis.

label.value: SLC39A4 wt Allele

value.value: Human SLC39A4 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 8q24.3 and is approximately 8 kb in length. This allele, which encodes zinc transporter ZIP4 protein, plays a role in cellular zinc homeostasis. Mutations in the gene are associated with acrodermatitis enteropathica.

label.value: Zinc Transporter ZIP4

value.value: Zinc transporter ZIP4 (647 aa, ~68 kDa) is encoded by the human SLC39A4 gene. This protein is involved in zinc ion transport.

label.value: Breath Carbon Monoxide Monitor

value.value: A device designed to measure carbon monoxide in a smoker's breath as a means toward smoking cessation.

label.value: CAGE1 Gene

value.value: This gene may play a role in testes development and carcinogenesis.

label.value: CAGE1 wt Allele

value.value: Human CAGE1 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 6p24.3 and is approximately 63 kb in length. This allele, which encodes cancer-associated gene 1 protein, may be involved in testes development and carcinogenesis. Aberrant expression is associated with several cancers.

label.value: Cancer-Associated Gene 1 Protein

value.value: Cancer-associated gene 1 protein (777 aa, ~90 kDa) is encoded by the human CAGE1 gene. This protein may play a role in testes development and carcinogenesis.

label.value: Ovarian, Fallopian Tube, and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma TNM Finding v8

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of ovarian, fallopian tube, or primary peritoneal carcinoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system. Nonepithelial primary ovarian cancers may be staged using this classification but should be reported separately. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian, Fallopian Tube, and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma Clinical TNM Finding v8

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of ovarian, fallopian tube, or primary peritoneal carcinoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system.

label.value: Ovarian, Fallopian Tube, and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma Clinical Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v8

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of ovarian, fallopian tube, or primary peritoneal carcinoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.

value.value: Ovarian, fallopian tube, or primary peritoneal carcinoma with distant metastasis, including pleural effusion with positive cytology; liver or splenic parenchymal metastasis; metastasis to extra-abdominal organs (including inguinal lymph nodes and lymph nodes outside the abdominal cavity); and transmural involvement of intestine. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian, Fallopian Tube, and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma cM1a TNM Finding v8

value.value: Ovarian, fallopian tube, or primary peritoneal carcinoma with pleural effusion with positive cytology. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian, Fallopian Tube, and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma cM1b TNM Finding v8

value.value: Ovarian, fallopian tube, or primary peritoneal carcinoma with liver or splenic parenchymal metastases; metastases to extra-abdominal organs (including inguinal lymph nodes and lymph nodes outside the abdominal cavity); transmural involvement of intestine. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian, Fallopian Tube, and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma Pathologic TNM Finding v8

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of ovarian, fallopian tube, or primary peritoneal carcinoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system.

label.value: Ovarian, Fallopian Tube, and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma Pathologic Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v8

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of ovarian, fallopian tube, or primary peritoneal carcinoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.

label.value: Ovarian, Fallopian Tube, and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma pM1 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Ovarian, fallopian tube, or primary peritoneal carcinoma with distant metastasis, including pleural effusion with positive cytology; liver or splenic parenchymal metastasis; metastasis to extra-abdominal organs (including inguinal lymph nodes and lymph nodes outside the abdominal cavity); and transmural involvement of intestine. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian, Fallopian Tube, and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma pM1a TNM Finding v8

value.value: Ovarian, fallopian tube, or primary peritoneal carcinoma with pleural effusion with positive cytology. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian, Fallopian Tube, and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma pM1b TNM Finding v8

value.value: Ovarian, fallopian tube, or primary peritoneal carcinoma with liver or splenic parenchymal metastases; metastases to extra-abdominal organs (including inguinal lymph nodes and lymph nodes outside the abdominal cavity); transmural involvement of intestine. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian, Fallopian Tube, and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma Pathologic Primary Tumor TNM Finding v8

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of ovarian, fallopian tube, or primary peritoneal carcinoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor. The definitions of the T categories correspond to the stages accepted by FIGO. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)
A chromosome band present on 12q

label.value: Ovarian, Fallopian Tube, and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma pTX TNM Finding v8

value.value: Ovarian, fallopian tube, or primary peritoneal carcinoma in which the primary tumor cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian, Fallopian Tube, and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma pT0 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Ovarian, fallopian tube, or primary peritoneal carcinoma with no evidence of primary tumor. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian, Fallopian Tube, and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma pT1 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Ovarian, fallopian tube, or primary peritoneal carcinoma with tumor limited to ovaries (one or both) or fallopian tube(s). (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian, Fallopian Tube, and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma pT1a TNM Finding v8

value.value: Ovarian, fallopian tube, or primary peritoneal carcinoma with tumor limited to one ovary (capsule intact) or fallopian tube surface; no malignant cells in ascites or peritoneal washings. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian, Fallopian Tube, and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma pT1b TNM Finding v8

value.value: Ovarian, fallopian tube, or primary peritoneal carcinoma with tumor limited to one or both ovaries (capsules intact) or fallopian tubes; no tumor on ovarian or fallopian tube surface; no malignant cells in ascites or peritoneal washings. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian, Fallopian Tube, and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma pT1c TNM Finding v8

value.value: Ovarian, fallopian tube, or primary peritoneal carcinoma with tumor limited to one or both ovaries or fallopian tubes, with any of the following: surgical spill, capsule ruptured before surgery or tumor on ovarian or fallopian tube surface, or malignant cells in ascites or peritoneal washings. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian, Fallopian Tube, and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma pT1c1 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Ovarian, fallopian tube, or primary peritoneal carcinoma with tumor limited to one or both ovaries or fallopian tubes, with surgical spill. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian, Fallopian Tube, and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma pT1c2 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Ovarian, fallopian tube, or primary peritoneal carcinoma with tumor limited to one or both ovaries or fallopian tubes, with capsule ruptured before surgery or tumor on ovarian or fallopian tube surface. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian, Fallopian Tube, and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma pT1c3 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Ovarian, fallopian tube, or primary peritoneal carcinoma with tumor limited to one or both ovaries or fallopian tubes with malignant cells in ascites or peritoneal washings. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian, Fallopian Tube, and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma pT2 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Ovarian, fallopian tube, or primary peritoneal carcinoma with tumor involving one or both ovaries or fallopian tubes with pelvic extension below pelvic brim or primary peritoneal cancer. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)
A chromosome band present on 9q

label.value: Ovarian, Fallopian Tube, and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma pT2a TNM Finding v8

value.value: Ovarian, fallopian tube, or primary peritoneal carcinoma with extension and/or implants on the uterus and/or fallopian tube(s) and/or ovaries. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian, Fallopian Tube, and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma pT2b TNM Finding v8

value.value: Ovarian, fallopian tube, or primary peritoneal carcinoma with extension to and/or implants on other pelvic tissues. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian, Fallopian Tube, and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma pT3 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Ovarian, fallopian tube, or primary peritoneal carcinoma with tumor involving one or both ovaries or fallopian tubes, or primary peritoneal cancer, with microscopically confirmed peritoneal metastasis outside the pelvis and/or metastasis to the retroperitoneal (pelvic and/or para-aortic) lymph nodes. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian, Fallopian Tube, and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma pT3a TNM Finding v8

value.value: Ovarian, fallopian tube, or primary peritoneal carcinoma with microscopic extrapelvic (above the pelvic brim) peritoneal involvement with or without positive retroperitoneal lymph nodes. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian, Fallopian Tube, and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma pT3b TNM Finding v8

value.value: Ovarian, fallopian tube, or primary peritoneal carcinoma with macroscopic peritoneal metastasis beyond pelvis 2 cm or less in greatest dimension with or without metastasis to the retroperitoneal lymph nodes. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian, Fallopian Tube, and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma pT3c TNM Finding v8

value.value: Ovarian, fallopian tube, or primary peritoneal carcinoma with macroscopic peritoneal metastasis beyond the pelvis more than 2 cm in greatest dimension with or without metastasis to the retroperitoneal lymph nodes (includes extension of tumor to capsule of liver and spleen without parenchymal involvement of either organ). (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian, Fallopian Tube, and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma Pathologic Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v8

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of ovarian, fallopian tube, or primary peritoneal carcinoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

label.value: Ovarian, Fallopian Tube, and Primary Peritoneal Carcinoma pNX TNM Finding v8

value.value: Ovarian, fallopian tube, or primary peritoneal carcinoma in which the regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)
